---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="NOFO Processor - JZ Stafura"
  description="AI-powered grant solicitation analysis tool. Extracts deadlines, eligibility, budget constraints, and generates preparation timelines."
>
  <div class="back"><a href="/lab/">&#x2190; Lab</a></div>

  <section class="hero">
    <p class="overline">Lab / Tool</p>
    <h1>NOFO Processor</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">AI-powered grant solicitation analysis for research administrators and faculty.</p>
    <div class="meta-row">
      <span class="status status-tool">Tool</span>
      <span class="origin">Originally built for the Learning Research and Development Center, University of Pittsburgh</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="what">
    <h2>What It Does</h2>
    <p>The NOFO Processor reads grant solicitations (NOFOs, RFAs, program announcements) and extracts the information that takes research administrators hours to compile manually.</p>
    <div class="feature-grid">
      <div class="feature">
        <strong>Extraction</strong>
        <p>All deadlines, eligibility rules, budget limits, submission caps, required documents, page limits, and compliance requirements &mdash; from a PDF upload or URL.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <strong>Critical Flags</strong>
        <p>Surfaces high-stakes issues immediately: per-institution submission limits, mandatory LOIs, F&amp;A caps below your negotiated rate, unusual eligibility restrictions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <strong>Timeline Generation</strong>
        <p>9-stage internal workflow with business day calculations. Dynamic: shows only future stages from today. Handles multi-window solicitations (e.g., NSF).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <strong>PI Summary Builder</strong>
        <p>Modular HTML documents with 14 toggleable sections. Personalization fields. Print to PDF. Configurable presets for "All Sections" or "Essentials Only."</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="how">
    <h2>How to Use It</h2>
    <p>The NOFO Processor is a <strong>Claude Skill</strong> &mdash; a detailed specification that Claude follows to build a configured, institution-specific tool in a single conversation. It is not a hosted web app; it runs as a Claude artifact.</p>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <span class="step-num">1</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Start a Claude conversation</strong>
          <p>Open Claude (claude.ai or API). Upload the SKILL.md file or reference it from a Claude Project.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <span class="step-num">2</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Provide your institutional rates</strong>
          <p>F&amp;A rates, fringe rates, equipment threshold, key contacts. Claude configures the tool to your institution.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <span class="step-num">3</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Upload a NOFO</strong>
          <p>Drop in any PDF solicitation. The tool extracts, flags, generates a timeline, and produces an exportable PI summary.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="contact-note">Interested in a live demo or adapting this for your institution? <a href="/consulting/">Get in touch</a>.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Stack</h2>
    <div class="tags">
      <span>Claude API</span>
      <span>React</span>
      <span>Prompt Engineering</span>
      <span>JSON Schema v3</span>
      <span>Grants Management</span>
    </div>
    <p class="version">Version 3.0 &mdash; February 2026</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .back { padding: 1.5rem 0 0; }
  .back a { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-muted); }
  .back a:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .overline { font-size: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .hero { padding: 2.5rem 0 2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .hero-sub { max-width: 55ch; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .meta-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1.5rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .status { font-size: 0.65rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 0.2rem 0.55rem; border: 1px solid; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .status-tool { color: var(--color-accent); border-color: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.3); background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.05); }
  .origin { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-muted); font-style: italic; }
  section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: 0.02em; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .what p { color: var(--color-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.7; max-width: 60ch; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .feature-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(240px, 1fr)); gap: 1.25rem; }
  .feature { padding: 1.25rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .feature strong { display: block; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .feature p { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-muted); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }
  .how p { color: var(--color-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.7; max-width: 60ch; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .how strong { color: var(--color-text); }
  .steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .step { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 3rem 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); align-items: start; }
  .step:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .step-num { font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-border); font-family: var(--font-mono); line-height: 1.4; }
  .step strong { display: block; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .step p { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-muted); margin: 0; line-height: 1.6; }
  .contact-note { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-muted); }
  .contact-note a { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .tags { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.4rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .tags span { font-size: 0.65rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-muted); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem; }
  .version { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-muted); }
</style>
